  <brief_title>Global Efficacy Study of MPC-7869 to Treat Patients With Alzheimer's</brief_title>
  <official_title>Phase 3 Multinational, Randomized, Double Blind, Placebo Controlled Study of the Effect of Daily Treatment With MPC-7869 on Measures of Cognition, Activities of Daily Living and Global Function in Subjects With Mild Dementia of the Alzheimer's Type</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Myrexis Inc.</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Myrexis Inc.</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a multinational, randomized, double blind, placebo controlled, parallel group study
      comparing the safety and efficacy of daily dosing of 800 mg twice daily MPC-7869 to placebo.
      Study subjects will have the diagnosis of mild dementia of the Alzheimer's type. Subjects may
      be taking approved medication for Alzheimer's disease provided the dose has been stable for
      at least 6 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
